#Thirst (#1085): aura - tap + doesn't untap + "at your upkeep sacrifice THIRST
#unless you pay {U}". Decline at my turn-3 upkeep: the AURA goes to the
#graveyard and the bears survive (the reported bug killed the creature).
[INIT]
firstmain
[PLAYER1]
manapool:{2}{U}
hand:thirst
inplay:grizzly bears
library:millstone,juggernaut
[PLAYER2]
library:millstone,juggernaut
[DO]
thirst
grizzly bears
goto firstmain
goto firstmain
goto end
goto firstmain
goto end
goto upkeep
goto upkeep
choice 1
goto upkeep
goto upkeep
[ASSERT]
UPKEEP
[PLAYER1]
graveyard:thirst
inplay:grizzly bears
library:millstone,juggernaut
tappedinplay:1
[PLAYER2]
hand:*
library:millstone
[END]
#PARKED: the granted upkeep cost is fully DEAD on master. Trace at my upkeep
#shows NO StackAbility from Thirst at all - the all(this) transforms((,
#newability[upcost[{U}] sacrifice])) grant never registers its AUpkeep (the
#234 direct auto=upcost users parse at load; the granted path doesn't wire
#the phase machinery). History: the complaint ("killed my creature") matches
#the OLD bare auto=upcost form, which - like all aura auto lines - applied to
#the ENCHANTED CREATURE; the all(this)-wrap stopped the creature kill but
#left the cost inert. No data fix available: pay[[{U}]]-in-trigger is the
#other engine wedge (round 1). Engine fuel: grant-machinery upcost
#registration + pay[[ stale-string. Current net behavior: Thirst is a free
#permanent tap-lock (tap + doesnotuntap legs DO work).
